                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 14:14", text: "Yahweh will fight for you, and you shall be still.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 15:2", text: "Yah is my strength and song. He has become my salvation. This is my God, and I will praise him; my father’s God, and I will exalt him.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 20:3", text: "“You shall have no other gods before me.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 20:12", text: "“Honor your father and your mother, that your days may be long in the land which Yahweh your God gives you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 20:13-17", text: "“You shall not murder. “You shall not commit adultery. “You shall not steal. “You shall not give false testimony against your neighbor. “You shall not covet your neighbor’s house. You shall not covet your neighbor’s wife, nor his male servant, nor his female servant, nor his ox, nor his donkey, nor anything that is your neighbor’s.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 23:25", text: "You shall serve Yahweh your God, and he will bless your bread and your water, and I will take sickness away from among you.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 33:14", text: "The Lord replied, \"My Presence will go with you, and I will give you rest.\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 34:6", text: "And he passed in front of Moses, proclaiming, \"The Lord, the Lord, the compassionate and gracious God, slow to anger, abounding in love and faithfulness.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 34:14", text: "for you shall worship no other god: for Yahweh, whose name is Jealous, is a jealous God.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 15:26", text: "He said, \"If you listen carefully to the Lord your God and do what is right in his eyes, if you pay attention to his commands and keep all his decrees, I will not bring on you any of the diseases I brought on the Egyptians, for I am the Lord, who heals you.\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 16:4", text: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \"I will rain down bread from heaven for you. The people are to go out each day and gather enough for that day.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 19:5", text: "Now therefore, if you will indeed obey my voice, and keep my covenant, then you shall be my own possession from among all peoples; for all the earth is mine;", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 31:3", text: "and I have filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom, and in understanding, and in knowledge, and in all kinds of workmanship,", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 40:34", text: "Then the cloud covered the Tent of Meeting, and Yahweh’s glory filled the tabernacle.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 2:24", text: "God heard their groaning, and God remembered his covenant with Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 6:7", text: "and I will take you to me for a people, and I will be to you a God; and you shall know that I am Yahweh your God, who brings you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 12:13", text: "The blood shall be to you for a token on the houses where you are: and when I see the blood, I will pass over you, and there shall no plague be on you to destroy you, when I strike the land of Egypt.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 13:21", text: "Yahweh went before them by day in a pillar of cloud, to lead them on their way, and by night in a pillar of fire, to give them light, that they might go by day and by night:", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 20:7", text: "“You shall not take the name of Yahweh your God in vain, for Yahweh will not hold him guiltless who takes his name in vain.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 20:8", text: "“Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 29:45", text: "I will dwell among the children of Israel, and will be their God.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 32:26", text: "So he stood at the entrance to the camp and said, \"Whoever is for the Lord, come to me.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Exodus 35:31", text: "He has filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom, in understanding, in knowledge, and in all kinds of workmanship;", translation: "WEB"),
        
        // Leviticus (146-165)
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 11:45", text: "For I am Yahweh who brought you up out of the land of Egypt, to be your God. You shall therefore be holy, for I am holy.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 19:2", text: "“Speak to all the congregation of the children of Israel, and tell them, ‘You shall be holy; for I, Yahweh your God, am holy.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 19:18", text: "“‘You shall not take vengeance, nor bear any grudge against the children of your people; but you shall love your neighbor as yourself. I am Yahweh.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 20:26", text: "You shall be holy to me; for I, Yahweh, am holy, and have set you apart from the peoples, that you should be mine.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 26:12", text: "I will walk among you, and will be your God, and you will be my people.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 27:30", text: "“‘All the tithe of the land, whether of the seed of the land or of the fruit of the trees, is Yahweh’s. It is holy to Yahweh.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 6:7", text: "The priest shall make atonement for him before Yahweh, and he will be forgiven concerning whatever he does to become guilty.”", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 10:3", text: "Moses then said to Aaron, \"This is what the Lord spoke of when he said: 'Among those who approach me I will be proved holy; in the sight of all the people I will be honored.'\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 16:30", text: "for on this day shall atonement be made for you, to cleanse you; from all your sins you shall be clean before Yahweh.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 17:11", text: "For the life of the flesh is in the blood; and I have given it to you on the altar to make atonement for your souls: for it is the blood that makes atonement by reason of the life.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 19:34", text: "The stranger who lives as a foreigner with you shall be to you as the native-born among you, and you shall love him as yourself; for you lived as foreigners in the land of Egypt. I am Yahweh your God.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 20:7-8", text: "“‘Sanctify yourselves therefore, and be holy; for I am Yahweh your God. You shall keep my statutes, and do them. I am Yahweh who sanctifies you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 22:31", text: "“Therefore you shall keep my commandments, and do them. I am Yahweh.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 23:22", text: "“‘When you reap the harvest of your land, you must not wholly reap into the corners of your field, and you must not gather the gleanings of your harvest. You must leave them for the poor, and for the foreigner. I am Yahweh your God.’”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 25:17", text: "You shall not wrong one another; but you shall fear your God: for I am Yahweh your God.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 26:13", text: "I am Yahweh your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, that you should not be their slaves. I have broken the bars of your yoke, and made you go upright.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 26:44-45", text: "Yet for all that, when they are in the land of their enemies, I will not reject them, neither will I abhor them, to destroy them utterly, and to break my covenant with them; for I am Yahweh their God; but I will for their sake remember the covenant of their ancestors, whom I brought out of the land of Egypt in the sight of the nations, that I might be their God. I am Yahweh.’”", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 9:6", text: "Moses said, \"This is what the Lord has commanded you to do, so that the glory of the Lord may appear to you.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 19:9", text: "“‘When you reap the harvest of your land, you shall not wholly reap the corners of your field, neither shall you gather the gleanings of your harvest.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Leviticus 19:15", text: "“‘You shall do no injustice in judgment. You shall not be partial to the poor, nor show favoritism to the great; but you shall judge your neighbor in righteousness.", translation: "WEB"),
        
        // Numbers (166-185)
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 6:24-26", text: "‘Yahweh bless you, and keep you. Yahweh make his face to shine on you, and be gracious to you. Yahweh lift up his face toward you, and give you peace.’", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 14:18", text: "‘Yahweh is slow to anger, and abundant in loving kindness, forgiving iniquity and disobedience; and he will by no means clear the guilty, visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children, on the third and on the fourth generation.’", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 23:19", text: "God is not a man, that he should lie, nor a son of man, that he should repent. Has he said, and will he not do it? Or has he spoken, and will he not make it good?", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 6:25", text: "Yahweh make his face to shine on you, and be gracious to you.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 11:23", text: "The Lord answered Moses, \"Is the Lord's arm too short? Now you will see whether or not what I say will come true for you.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 14:8", text: "If Yahweh delights in us, then he will bring us into this land, and give it to us; a land which flows with milk and honey.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 21:9", text: "Moses made a serpent of brass, and set it on the pole. If a serpent had bitten any man, when he looked at the serpent of brass, he lived.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 22:12", text: "But God said to Balaam, \"Do not go with them. You must not put a curse on those people, because they are blessed.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 23:8", text: "How shall I curse whom God has not cursed? How shall I defy whom Yahweh has not defied?", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 24:5", text: "How goodly are your tents, Jacob, and your tents, Israel!", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 13:30", text: "Then Caleb silenced the people before Moses and said, \"We should go up and take possession of the land, for we can certainly do it.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 14:9", text: "Only don’t rebel against Yahweh, neither fear the people of the land; for they are bread for us. Their defense is removed from over them, and Yahweh is with us. Don’t fear them.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 15:40", text: "so that you may remember and do all my commandments, and be holy to your God.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 16:48", text: "He stood between the dead and the living; and the plague was stayed.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 20:12", text: "But the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, \"Because you did not trust in me enough to honor me as holy in the sight of the Israelites, you will not bring this community into the land I give them.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 21:4", text: "They traveled from Mount Hor by the way to the Red Sea, to go around the land of Edom The soul of the people was very discouraged because of the journey.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 22:38", text: "\"Well, I have come to you now,\" Balaam replied. \"But I can't say whatever I please. I must speak only what God puts in my mouth.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 24:17", text: "I see him, but not now. I see him, but not near. A star will come out of Jacob. A scepter will rise out of Israel, and shall strike through the corners of Moab, and break down all the sons of Sheth.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 27:18", text: "So the Lord said to Moses, \"Take Joshua son of Nun, a man in whom is the spirit of leadership, and lay your hand on him.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Numbers 32:23", text: "“But if you will not do so, behold, you have sinned against Yahweh; and be sure your sin will find you out.", translation: "WEB"),
        
        // Deuteronomy (186-220)
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 6:4-5", text: "Hear, Israel: Yahweh is our God. Yahweh is one. You shall love Yahweh your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your might.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 6:7", text: "and you shall teach them diligently to your children, and shall talk of them when you sit in your house, and when you walk by the way, and when you lie down, and when you rise up.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 7:9", text: "Know therefore that Yahweh your God himself is God, the faithful God, who keeps covenant and loving kindness with them who love him and keep his commandments to a thousand generations,", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 10:12", text: "Now, Israel, what does Yahweh your God require of you, but to fear Yahweh your God, to walk in all his ways, and to love him, and to serve Yahweh your God with all your heart and with all your soul,", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 10:17", text: "For Yahweh your God, he is God of gods, and Lord of lords, the great God, the mighty, and the awesome, who doesn’t respect persons, nor takes reward.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 11:26-28", text: "Behold, I set before you today a blessing and a curse: the blessing, if you listen to the commandments of Yahweh your God, which I command you today; and the curse, if you do not listen to the commandments of Yahweh your God, but turn away out of the way which I command you today, to go after other gods, which you have not known.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 28:2", text: "All these blessings will come upon you, and overtake you, if you listen to Yahweh your God’s voice.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 30:19-20", text: "I call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that I have set before you life and death, the blessing and the curse. Therefore choose life, that you may live, you and your descendants; to love Yahweh your God, to obey his voice, and to cling to him; for he is your life, and the length of your days; that you may dwell in the land which Yahweh swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give them.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 31:8", text: "Yahweh himself is who goes before you. He will be with you. He will not fail you nor forsake you. Don’t be afraid. Don’t be discouraged.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 32:4", text: "The Rock, his work is perfect, for all his ways are just. A God of faithfulness who does no wrong, just and right is he.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 33:27", text: "The eternal God is your dwelling place. Underneath are the everlasting arms. He thrust out the enemy from before you, and said, ‘Destroy!’", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 4:2", text: "You shall not add to the word which I command you, neither shall you take away from it, that you may keep the commandments of Yahweh your God which I command you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 4:24", text: "For Yahweh your God is a devouring fire, a jealous God.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 4:31", text: "For Yahweh your God is a merciful God. He will not fail you, neither destroy you, nor forget the covenant of your fathers which he swore to them.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 5:33", text: "You shall walk in all the way which Yahweh your God has commanded you, that you may live, and that it may be well with you, and that you may prolong your days in the land which you shall possess.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 8:2", text: "You shall remember all the way which Yahweh your God has led you these forty years in the wilderness, that he might humble you, to prove you, to know what was in your heart, whether you would keep his commandments, or not.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 8:3", text: "He humbled you, and allowed you to be hungry, and fed you with manna, which you didn’t know, neither did your fathers know; that he might teach you that man does not live by bread only, but man lives by every word that proceeds out of Yahweh’s mouth.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 13:4", text: "You shall walk after Yahweh your God, fear him, keep his commandments, and obey his voice, and you shall serve him, and cling to him.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 13:18", text: "when you listen to Yahweh your God’s voice, to keep all his commandments which I command you today, to do that which is right in Yahweh your God’s eyes.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 14:2", text: "For you are a holy people to Yahweh your God, and Yahweh has chosen you to be a people for his own possession, above all peoples who are on the face of the earth.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 16:20", text: "You shall follow that which is altogether just, that you may live, and inherit the land which Yahweh your God gives you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 17:20", text: "that his heart not be lifted up above his brothers, and that he not turn away from the commandment, to the right hand, or to the left; to the end that he may prolong his days in his kingdom, he and his children, in the middle of Israel.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 18:13", text: "You shall be perfect with Yahweh your God.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 18:15", text: "Yahweh your God will raise up to you a prophet from among you, of your brothers, like me. You shall listen to him.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 20:4", text: "for Yahweh your God is he who goes with you, to fight for you against your enemies, to save you.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 23:5", text: "Nevertheless Yahweh your God wouldn’t listen to Balaam; but Yahweh your God turned the curse into a blessing to you, because Yahweh your God loved you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 26:18", text: "Yahweh has declared today that you are a people for his own possession, as he has promised you, and that you should keep all his commandments.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 29:29", text: "The secret things belong to Yahweh our God; but the things that are revealed belong to us and to our children forever, that we may do all the words of this law.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Deuteronomy 31:6", text: "Be strong and courageous. Don’t be afraid or scared of them; for Yahweh your God himself is who goes with you. He will not fail you nor forsake you.”", translation: "WEB"),
        
        // ========== OLD TESTAMENT - Historical Books ==========
        
        // Joshua (221-240)
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 1:8", text: "This book of the law shall not depart from your mouth, but you shall meditate on it day and night, that you may observe to do according to all that is written in it; for then you shall make your way prosperous, and then you shall have good success.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 1:9", text: "Haven’t I commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Don’t be afraid. Don’t be dismayed, for Yahweh your God is with you wherever you go.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 24:15", text: "If it seems evil to you to serve Yahweh, choose today whom you will serve; whether the gods which your fathers served that were beyond the River, or the gods of the Amorites, in whose land you dwell; but as for me and my house, we will serve Yahweh.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 1:5", text: "No man will be able to stand before you all the days of your life. As I was with Moses, so I will be with you. I will not fail you nor forsake you.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 3:5", text: "Joshua told the people, \"Consecrate yourselves, for tomorrow the Lord will do amazing things among you.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 7:13", text: "“Get up! Sanctify the people, and say, ‘Sanctify yourselves for tomorrow, for Yahweh, the God of Israel, says, “There is a devoted thing among you, Israel. You cannot stand before your enemies until you take away the devoted thing from among you.”", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 10:25", text: "Joshua said to them, \"Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged. Be strong and courageous. This is what the Lord will do to all the enemies you are going to fight.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 14:8", text: "Nevertheless, my brothers who went up with me made the heart of the people melt; but I wholly followed Yahweh my God.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 21:45", text: "Nothing failed of any good thing which Yahweh had spoken to the house of Israel. All came to pass.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 22:5", text: "Only take diligent heed to do the commandment and the law which Moses the servant of Yahweh commanded you, to love Yahweh your God, to walk in all his ways, to keep his commandments, to hold fast to him, and to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 23:3", text: "You have seen all that Yahweh your God has done to all these nations because of you; for it is Yahweh your God who has fought for you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 23:10", text: "One man of you shall chase a thousand; for it is Yahweh your God who fights for you, as he spoke to you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 23:14", text: "“Behold, today I am going the way of all the earth. You know in all your hearts and in all your souls that not one thing has failed of all the good things which Yahweh your God spoke concerning you. All have happened to you. Not one thing has failed of it.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 4:24", text: "that all the peoples of the earth may know that Yahweh’s hand is mighty; that you may fear Yahweh your God forever.’”", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 5:15", text: "The commander of the Lord's army replied, \"Take off your sandals, for the place where you are standing is holy.\" And Joshua did so.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 8:1", text: "Then the Lord said to Joshua, \"Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged. Take the whole army with you, and go up and attack Ai.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 11:23", text: "So Joshua took the whole land, according to all that Yahweh spoke to Moses; and Joshua gave it for an inheritance to Israel according to their divisions by their tribes. The land had rest from war.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 13:1", text: "When Joshua had grown old, the Lord said to him, \"You are now very old, and there are still very large areas of land to be taken over.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 17:18", text: "but the hill country shall be yours. Although it is a forest, you shall cut it down, and it’s farthest extent shall be yours; for you shall drive out the Canaanites, though they have chariots of iron, and though they are strong.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Joshua 22:34", text: "The children of Reuben and the children of Gad named the altar “A Witness Between Us that Yahweh is God.”", translation: "WEB"),
        
        // Judges (241-255)
                BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 2:18", text: "When Yahweh raised up judges for them, then Yahweh was with the judge, and saved them out of the hand of their enemies all the days of the judge; for it grieved Yahweh because of their groaning by reason of those who oppressed them and troubled them.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 6:12", text: "When the angel of the Lord appeared to Gideon, he said, \"The Lord is with you, mighty warrior.\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 6:14", text: "The Lord turned to him and said, \"Go in the strength you have and save Israel out of Midian's hand. Am I not sending you?\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 6:16", text: "The Lord answered, \"I will be with you, and you will strike down all the Midianites, leaving none alive.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 13:24", text: "The woman bore a son, and named him Samson. The child grew, and Yahweh blessed him.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 16:28", text: "Then Samson prayed to the Lord, \"Sovereign Lord, remember me. Please, God, strengthen me just once more, and let me with one blow get revenge on the Philistines for my two eyes.\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 17:6", text: "In those days there was no king in Israel. Everyone did that which was right in his own eyes.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 21:25", text: "In those days there was no king in Israel. Everyone did that which was right in his own eyes.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 3:10", text: "Yahweh’s Spirit came on him, and he judged Israel; and he went out to war, and Yahweh delivered Cushan Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into his hand. His hand prevailed against Cushan Rishathaim.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 4:14", text: "Then Deborah said to Barak, \"Go! This is the day the Lord has given Sisera into your hands. Has not the Lord gone ahead of you?\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 5:2", text: "“Because the leaders took the lead in Israel, because the people offered themselves willingly, be blessed, Yahweh!", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Judges 7:2", text: "The Lord said to Gideon, \"You have too many men. I cannot deliver Midian into their hands, or Israel would boast against me, 'My own strength has saved me.'\"", translation: "WEB"),
