        // Isaiah - Major Prophet (786-850) - 65 verses
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 1:18", text: "\"Come now, let us settle the matter,\" says the Lord. \"Though your sins are like scarlet, they shall be as white as snow; though they are red as crimson, they shall be like wool.\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 6:3", text: "And they were calling to one another: \"Holy, holy, holy is the Lord Almighty; the whole earth is full of his glory.\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 6:8", text: "Then I heard the voice of the Lord saying, \"Whom shall I send? And who will go for us?\" And I said, \"Here am I. Send me!\"", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 7:14", text: "Therefore the Lord himself will give you a sign. Behold, the virgin will conceive, and bear a son, and shall call his name Immanuel.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 9:2", text: "The people who walked in darkness have seen a great light. Those who lived in the land of the shadow of death, on them the light has shined.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 9:6", text: "For to us a child is born. To us a son is given; and the government will be on his shoulders. His name will be called Wonderful, Counselor, Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 11:2", text: "Yahweh’s Spirit will rest on him: the spirit of wisdom and understanding, the spirit of counsel and might, the spirit of knowledge and of the fear of Yahweh.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 12:2", text: "Behold, God is my salvation. I will trust, and will not be afraid; for Yah, Yahweh, is my strength and song; and he has become my salvation.”", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 25:1", text: "Yahweh, you are my God. I will exalt you! I will praise your name, for you have done wonderful things, things planned long ago, in complete faithfulness and truth.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 26:3", text: "You will keep whoever’s mind is steadfast in perfect peace, because he trusts in you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 26:4", text: "Trust in Yahweh forever; for in Yah, Yahweh, is an everlasting Rock.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 30:15", text: "This is what the Sovereign Lord, the Holy One of Israel, says: \"In repentance and rest is your salvation, in quietness and trust is your strength, but you would have none of it.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 30:18", text: "Therefore Yahweh will wait, that he may be gracious to you; and therefore he will be exalted, that he may have mercy on you, for Yahweh is a God of justice. Blessed are all those who wait for him.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 31:1", text: "Woe to those who go down to Egypt for help, and rely on horses, and trust in chariots because they are many, and in horsemen because they are very strong, but they don’t look to the Holy One of Israel, and they don’t seek Yahweh!", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 32:17", text: "The work of righteousness will be peace; and the effect of righteousness, quietness and confidence forever.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 33:2", text: "Yahweh, be gracious to us. We have waited for you. Be our strength every morning, our salvation also in the time of trouble.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 35:4", text: "say to those with fearful hearts, \"Be strong, do not fear; your God will come, he will come with vengeance; with divine retribution he will come to save you.\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 40:3", text: "A voice of one calling: \"In the wilderness prepare the way for the Lord; make straight in the desert a highway for our God.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 40:5", text: "And the glory of the Lord will be revealed, and all people will see it together. For the mouth of the Lord has spoken.\"", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 40:6", text: "A voice says, \"Cry out.\" And I said, \"What shall I cry?\" \"All people are like grass, and all their faithfulness is like the flowers of the field.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 40:10", text: "Behold, the Lord Yahweh will come as a mighty one, and his arm will rule for him. Behold, his reward is with him, and his recompense before him.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 40:11", text: "He will feed his flock like a shepherd. He will gather the lambs in his arm, and carry them in his bosom. He will gently lead those who have their young.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 40:28", text: "Haven’t you known? Haven’t you heard? The everlasting God, Yahweh, The Creator of the ends of the earth, doesn’t faint. He isn’t weary. His understanding is unsearchable.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 40:29", text: "He gives power to the weak. He increases the strength of him who has no might.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 41:10", text: "Don’t you be afraid, for I am with you. Don’t be dismayed, for I am your God. I will strengthen you. Yes, I will help you. Yes, I will uphold you with the right hand of my righteousness.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 41:13", text: "For I, Yahweh your God, will hold your right hand, saying to you, ‘Don’t be afraid. I will help you.’", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 43:1", text: "But now, this is what the Lord says—he who created you, Jacob, he who formed you, Israel: \"Do not fear, for I have redeemed you; I have summoned you by name; you are mine.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 43:2", text: "When you pass through the waters, I will be with you; and through the rivers, they will not overflow you. When you walk through the fire, you will not be burned, and flame will not scorch you.", translation: "WEB"),
