                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 43:11", text: "I myself am Yahweh; and besides me there is no savior.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 43:25", text: "I, even I, am he who blots out your transgressions for my own sake; and I will not remember your sins.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 44:3", text: "For I will pour water on him who is thirsty, and streams on the dry ground. I will pour my Spirit on your descendants, and my blessing on your offspring:", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 44:6", text: "This is what Yahweh, the King of Israel, and his Redeemer, Yahweh of Armies, says: “I am the first, and I am the last; and besides me there is no God.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 44:22", text: "I have blotted out, as a thick cloud, your transgressions, and, as a cloud, your sins. Return to me, for I have redeemed you.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 45:5", text: "I am Yahweh, and there is no one else. Besides me, there is no God. I will strengthen you, though you have not known me;", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 46:4", text: "Even to old age I am he, and even to gray hairs I will carry you. I have made, and I will bear. Yes, I will carry, and will deliver.", translation: "WEB"),
        BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 48:17", text: "This is what the Lord says—your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel: \"I am the Lord your God, who teaches you what is best for you, who directs you in the way you should go.", translation: "WEB"),
                BibleVerse(reference: "Isaiah 49:15", text: "“Can a woman forget her nursing child, that she should not have compassion on the son of her womb? Yes, these may forget, yet I will not forget you!", translation: "WEB"),
